<DATE>950323</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Luddon wins BP contract</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>3</PAGE>
<FLAG>SCOTLANDS BUSINESS</FLAG>
<RECORDNO>979255429</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
GLASGOW-based Luddon Construction has won the #1.5m maintenance
contract for BP Chemicals' 500-acre site at Grangemouth for the eighth
year in a row.
The civil engineering company had to fight its corner in a competitive
tendering situation.
Luddon has also received BP Chemicals' safety award for its work at
Grangemouth over the past year. Its operatives worked more than 80,000
man hours with only one minor injury.
Mr Charlie Frize, contracts director of Luddon Construction, said:
''We are delighted to continue to work with BP Chemicals. This is a very
important contract and we are pleased to win it on merit.''
</TEXT>
</DOC>
