<TEXT>
* Labour yesterday demanded that councils be given special powers to
designate housing crisis areas in Scotland.
Mr John McAllion, the party's housing spokesman, also called for
legislation to help deal with the problem of homelessness.
''The continuing scandal of half a million Scots living with dampness
in their homes, with all the spin-offs in terms of ill health, is one
which needs to be urgently addressed,'' he said.
