<DOCNO>GH950323-000006</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH950323-000006</DOCID>
<DATE>950323</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Fife firm expands</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>3</PAGE>
<FLAG>SCOTLANDS BUSINESS</FLAG>
<RECORDNO>979255434</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
FORMER racing driver Bryce Wilson (pictured left in his racing days)
has stepped his Fife-based engineering company up a gear.
The former Ferrari Formula 2 driver, who set up TF Fabrication in
Glenrothes four years ago, believes the expansion into recession-hit
North-east Fife will boost his workforce of 18 to more than 50 by the
end of next year.
TF's move into 53,000sq ft premises in Tayport is receiving financial
backing from Fife Regional Council and North East Fife District Council.
Operations at Tayport, which will focus on the offshore, civil and
structural markets, start on Monday.
</TEXT>
