<HEADLINE>Stakes raised</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>5</PAGE>
<FLAG>SCOTLANDS BUSINESS</FLAG>
<RECORDNO>979255457</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
MIRROR Group and Tony O'Reilly's Independent Newspapers have increased
their stakes in the loss-making newspaper the Independent to 43% each.
As part of the restructuring, the newspaper's Italian shareholders
will sell their 20% stake in the Newspaper Publishing Group, publisher
of the Independent and the Independent on Sunday, to MGN and Independent
Newspapers.
The Spanish shareholder El Pais-publisher (Prisa) will see its stake
fall to 12% from 18%.
Together Mirror Group, Independent Newspapers and Prisa will subscribe
for some #20m of new equity capital in Newspaper Publishing in the
proportion of 45-45-10.
