<TEXT>
Albion Rovers 1, Montrose 4
MONTROSE went ahead in seven minutes when Colin McGlashan headed home.
Mark Haro was on the mark after 23 minutes when he bulleted a 35-yard
free-kick past Alan Davidson.
Rovers pulled a goal back through Alex McEwan with 16 minutes
remaining but three minutes later Shaun Smith extended Montrose's lead
and just before full time the same player completed the scoring.
