<HEADLINE>Levein may miss vital qualifier</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>29</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>979255461</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
HEARTS defender Craig Levein is doubtful for Scotland's European
Championship qualifier against Russia in Moscow next week.
Levein suffered an ankle injury in the 1-1 draw with Dundee United on
Tuesday and, although he played the full 90 minutes, there are fears
there could be ligament damage. ''It's touch and go,'' admitted Hearts
manager Tommy McLean.
Defender Steve Frail will see a specialist after being stretchered off
at Tannadice with a knee injury. The extent of his injury is not yet
known, but the signs are that the cruciate ligament has not been damaged
and McLean has not given up hope of him being fit to face Airdrie in the
Scottish Cup semi-final next month.
''It will be 48 hours before we know,'' continued McLean. ''We have to
wait until the swelling and the bruising have died down.''
John Robertson, who was stretchered off with a knee injury against
Rangers on Saturday, is improving.
</TEXT>
