<HEADLINE>The finer points</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>18</PAGE>
<ARTICLETYPE>CORRESPONDENCE</ARTICLETYPE>
<RECORDNO>979255525</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
THE Diary about the Rev Donald John Macaskill brought to mind an
occasion when I worshipped in the Free Presbyterian Church in Uig,
Lewis, while visiting relatives who were members of his congregation
(March 21).
My limited Gaelic was not up to appreciating the finer points of his
45-minute sermon. However, I need not have worried. At the end of the
sermon he announced that as there was a visitor present he would just go
over the main points again in English -- and proceeded to do so for the
next half-hour.
I sensed that not everyone appreciated this courtesy. My hosts did not
encourage me to attend the evening service.
Finlay A J Macdonald,
96 Southbrae Drive,
Glasgow.
</TEXT>
