<TEXT>
MOTHERWELL District is a dream location for any company to which
communications and distribution are of any importance.
At the heart of Scotland's motorway system and with fast access to
local, national and international markets, it is within easy reach of
both Edinburgh and Glasgow (about 45 and 20 minutes' drive
respectively).
It offers business locations which have direct access to the M8, M73
and M74, bringing about 70% of Scotland's population within an hour's
travelling time.
That means easy and uncomplicated access to 3,000,000 consumers to
north, south, east and west.
Motherwell is only four-and-a-half hours from London, thanks to the
main electrified Glasgow-London route, the Eurocentral Scotland Freight
Terminal at Mossend provides direct access to the rapidly growing
markets on the Continent, and Glasgow and Edinburgh airports are both
about 30 minutes away, in opposite directions on the M8.
Europe and its 320 million consumers have simply never been closer and
the accessibility of air links makes the world their oyster for a
significant number of companies based in the district. Even Prestwick
Airport is only about an hour's drive away, and it boasts faster airport
clearance than any of its UK rivals.
Companies which have selected Motherwell District as the ideal
distribution centre include Safeway (who built Europe's biggest
warehouse facility), TNT Group and Royal Mail Parcels (both at Righead
Industrial Estate), Frigoscandia, and Geest UK. And earlier this month
it was announced that the Royal Mail was at an advanced stage of
negotiations with the district council for the establishment of a
Scottish Distribution Centre at Excelsior Park, Wishaw.
Those with manufacturing bases include Levi Strauss (UK) Ltd,
Motherwell Bridge Holdings, Anderson Group Ltd, Terex Equipment Ltd,
Cummin's Engine Co Ltd, Daiwa Sports Ltd, and award-winning export
engineers Calcarb Ltd.
It is important that suitable shopping facilities are available to all
who work at such companies, whether they live in the district or not,
and both the public and private sector have invested heavily in
Motherwell, Wishaw and Bellshill town centres in recent years, with
#33.9m spent in the period from 1977-91.
Some significant further investment is planned. Motherwell and Wishaw
town centres are expected to benefit from further private-sector
expenditure and #3.7m of public-sector expenditure.
</TEXT>
