<DOCID>GH950323-000116</DOCID>
<DATE>950323</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Schindler thanks</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>8</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>979255544</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
VATICAN CITY: The Pope yesterday thanked the widow of Oskar Schindler,
made famous in the film Schindler's List, for helping her husband to
save more than a thousand Polish Jews from Nazi death camps. The Pope
told 87-year-old Emilie Schindler: ''I know what you and your husband
did and the Polish people are grateful.'' Mrs Schindler said later that
she was very moved and joked with reporters that her husband was much
more handsome than Liam Neeson, who played him in the film.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO>GH950323-000117</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH950323-000117</DOCID>
<DATE>950323</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Class shoot-out</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>8</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>979255545</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
TUNIS: Six pupils were wounded and three gunmen killed when Muslim
guerrillas and Algerian security forces fought a gun battle in a crowded
Algiers school during classes yesterday. In London, leaders of Algerian
opposition groups urged the Tunis Government to accept a peace proposal
to end strife that has killed more than 30,000 people since 1992.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO>GH950323-000118</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH950323-000118</DOCID>
<DATE>950323</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Farmer freed</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>8</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>979255546</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
NICOSIA: A Greek Cypriot farmer jailed two weeks ago by a British
court for growing potatoes near a firing range in Cyprus was released
yesterday on humanitarian grounds. Chambis Chimonas, who ended a 13-day
hunger strike on Monday, agreed to respect a court order requiring him
to remove crops from the area. However he argues that the land belongs
to Cypriots.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO>GH950323-000119</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH950323-000119</DOCID>
<DATE>950323</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Mission over</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>8</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>979255547</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
MOSCOW: Russian cosmonaut Valery Polyakov returned to Earth yesterday
after a record-breaking 438 days in space. He and two other crew members
from the Russian space station Mir landed in Kazakhstan aboard a Soyuz
TM-20 craft. Polyakov, 52, broke the endurance record of one year in
space on January 9. He used himself as a guinea pig to test the
long-term effects of weightlessness on the body and the results will
help assess whether to send humans to Mars.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO>GH950323-000120</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH950323-000120</DOCID>
<DATE>950323</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Three executed</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>8</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>979255548</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
DUBAI: Two Pakistanis and a Chadian were beheaded in Saudi Arabia
yesterday for smuggling heroin. At least 15 people have been executed
this month for offences including murder, making and drinking alcohol,
and witchcraft.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO>GH950323-000121</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH950323-000121</DOCID>
<DATE>950323</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Envoys recalled</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>8</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>979255549</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
MANILA: The Philippines and Singapore recalled their ambassadors
yesterday as relations between the two countries plummeted to their
lowest depths in a row over the hanging of a Filipina maid. President
Fidel Ramos also banned any more maids from going to Singapore in the
crisis over last week's hanging of Flor Contemplacion.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO>GH950323-000122</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH950323-000122</DOCID>
<DATE>950323</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Plan for island</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>8</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>979255550</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
PARIS: The French Government has announced a seven-year, #68m plan to
prevent one of its most popular tourist attractions, the Mont Saint
Michel off the Brittany Coast, from silting up and becoming part of the
mainland. The island abbey, which is visited by 3.3 million people a
year, is still cut off by the sea at high tide, but the 1.3 mile-long
causeway built in 1878 prevents sand from being washed away.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO>GH950323-000123</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH950323-000123</DOCID>
<DATE>950323</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Japan tremor</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>8</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>979255551</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
TOKYO: A moderate earthquake measuring 4.6 on the Richter scale shook
Tokyo yesterday but there were no reports of damage, authorities said. A
stronger tremor of 5.9 was felt all along New Zealand early today, again
causing no serious damage.
</TEXT>
