<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>4</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>979255566</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
THE Scottish Ambulance Service yesterday announced the appointment of
five members who will spearhead its executive board. They have all been
chosen from the trust's existing management team. The executive board
comprises Mr Andrew Freemantle, the first general manager of the
service, consultant medical director Andrew Marsden, logistics director
Clive Wooller, finance director Brian Roy, and personnel director John
Bateman.
