<DATE>950323</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Churchmen meet</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>4</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>979255568</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
LEADING Anglican churchmen and lay members have been meeting at
Carberry Tower, in Musselburgh, over the past few days to map out the
Church's future work priorities for decades to come.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO>GH950323-000140</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH950323-000140</DOCID>
<DATE>950323</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Polish award</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>4</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>979255569</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
OFFICIALS from Edinburgh District Council will be presented today with
a planning award by the European Commission in Brussels. With colleagues
in Poland and Berlin, Edinburgh planners drew up a plan to revitalise
Kazimierz, the old Jewish quarter of Krakow, which was the home of many
of the workers in Oscar Schindler's factory.
</TEXT>
