<TEXT>
* UP TO 1800 jobs could be cut as a result of Scotland's council
reorganisation, the Government confirmed last night.
Mr Kynoch said in a written reply: ''The numbers of staff employed
will depend on decisions yet to be made by the new authorities.
''But, overall, it is estimated that local government reorganisation
could lead to a reduction of between 200 and 1800 in the present
workforce of around 300,000.''
