<DOCID>GH950323-000159</DOCID>
<DATE>950323</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Getting a head start on Portillo</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>FRANCES HORSBURGH, LOCAL GOVERNMENT CORRESPONDENT</BYLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>9</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>979255588</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
LABOUR'S Shadow Heritage Secretary Chris Smith pointed towards the
bust of an alien Klingon in a glass case. ''Bears a surprising
resemblance to Michael Portillo,'' he smiled.
Captain Kirk's deadly enemies are well represented at Edinburgh
District Council's Star Trek exhibition in the capital. Any resemblance
they bear to Tory Ministers is, of course, only in the eyes of the
beholder.
Mr Smith was touring some of the council's arts and leisure facilities
yesterday to help boost Labour's local campaign to win control of the
new single-tier Edinburgh city council.
On the issue of the National Lottery and the cash contribution it
could make to the arts and heritage, he said Labour wanted to see more
flexibility over the way the money was used.
</TEXT>
