<DOCNO>GH950323-000162</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH950323-000162</DOCID>
<DATE>950323</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Castrate all rapists call</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>6</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>979255591</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
A TORY MP last night demanded castration for convicted rapists as he
urged Home Secretary Michael Howard to get tougher on crime.
Mr David Evans (Welwyn and Hatfield) was intervening in a short
Commons debate on penalties for crime in which fellow Conservatives
complained about lenient sentencing.
Calling for Mr Howard to show his true colours, the MP demanded: ''He
should get hanging restored, and corporal punishment and castration for
all rapists -- yes, if anyone is raped, castrate them.''
He added: ''When are we going to start having Conservative principles
and not the wishy-washy politics of Labour?''
</TEXT>
