<DOCNO>GH950323-000187</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH950323-000187</DOCID>
<DATE>950323</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Overdose theory in deaths</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>5</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>979255616</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
A YOUNG couple, found dead in a neighbouring flat to the one in which
the body of a convicted child molester was discovered last month, may
have died from an overdose of painkillers.
Police officers had to break into the home of Mr Steven Charleston,
26, and his wife Karen, 25, at Southhouse Medway, Edinburgh after
relatives became concerned after they had not been seen for a while.
The couple's three-year-old daughter Charmaine is being looked after
by Mr Charleston's mother. It emerged yesterday that Karen Charleston
was not pregnant as had been reported.
Police have ruled out any link to the alleged killing of neighbour
Lawrence Leydon, 36, found dead last month.
The full results of the post-mortem examinations being carried out on
the couple are expected to take some time.
* Earlier this month, Mr Paul Strathearn, 33, of Buchanan Street, off
Leith Walk, appeared on petition at the city's sheriff court charged
with Mr Leydon's murder. The case was continued for further inquiries
and Mr Strathearn was remanded in custody.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO>GH950323-000188</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH950323-000188</DOCID>
<DATE>950323</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Farmer is killed in two-car crash</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>4</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>979255617</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
FARMER Mr James Paterson, 77, of Carnbo, Kinross, was killed last
night when his truck and an unmarked police car were in collision on the
A977 Kincardine Bridge-Kinross road.
Four Northern Constabulary officers were injured. Sergeant Malcolm
Buchanan, 44, of Nairn, and Constable John Finnie, 38, from Inverness,
were in Perth Royal Infirmary with serious abdominal injuries, while
Sergeant Edwin Graham, 28, of Dingwall, and Sergeant Robert Drummond,
37, from Inverness, were released after treatment for minor injuries.
</TEXT>
