<TEXT>
LABOUR has a 32% lead over the Tories, according to a poll published
today -- and Mr Tony Blair's approval rating is the highest since he
became party leader.
A Mori survey for The Times puts Labour on 57% (compared with 58% in
late February), the Conservatives on 25% (24%) and the Liberal Democrats
on 13% (14%).
The poll shows 51% are satisfied with the way Mr Blair is doing his
job (48% last month) while 21% are dissatisfied (22%). Among Labour
supporters, 70% are satisfied and 10% dissatisfied.
</TEXT>
